      • getFlowPartMessageText

        public String getFlowPartMessageText()
        Reads the readable text associated with the flow packet from the database.
        Returns:
        The readable text of the flow packet. If such does not exist, returns null.

      • setFlowPartMessageText

        public void setFlowPartMessageText(String message)
        Sets the readable text representation of the flow packet. If the message is null, after the current transaction is committed the existing message in the database (if such exists) will be deleted.
        Parameters:
        message - the text associated with the packet of this flow.
